
---


@startuml

' Define classes
class User {
    - id: int
    - name: string
    - birthday: date
    - address: string
}

class BusinessOwner {
    - linkedin: string
}

class PizzaRestaurant {
    - zipcode: string
    - address: string
    - phone: string
    - website: string
    - openingHours: string
}

class Pizza {
    - name: string
    - crustStructure: string
    - price: float
}

class Order {
    - orderId: int
    - dateTimePlaced: datetime
    - deliveryTimeLatest: datetime
    - numberOfPeople: int
}

class EntertainmentOrder {
    - typeOfEntertainment: string
    - duration: int  // in minutes
}

class Entertainer {
    - stageName: string
    - bio: string
    - pricePer30Min: float
}

class HungryCustomer {
    - deliveryAddress: string
}

' Relationships

User <|-- BusinessOwner
User <|-- HungryCustomer
User <|-- Entertainer

BusinessOwner "1" -- "0..*" PizzaRestaurant : owns

PizzaRestaurant "1" -- "0..*" Pizza : offers

HungryCustomer "1" -- "0..*" Order : makes

Order "1" -- "0..1" EntertainmentOrder : can be an
Order "1" -- "1" PizzaRestaurant : belongs to
Order "1" -- "1..*" Pizza : contains

Entertainer "1" -- "0..*" PizzaRestaurant : works at
Entertainer "*" -- "1" EntertainmentOrder : fulfills

PizzaRestaurant "*" -- "0..*" Entertainer : has

PizzaRestaurant "1" -- "1" Address : located at

note right of PizzaRestaurant
    Each pizza restaurant must have a unique combination of address and zip code.
end note

note right of Pizza
    Pizzas are uniquely identified by the restaurant they belong to, even if names or prices are the same elsewhere.
end note

@enduml

---

### 🧾 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **User** is the base class from which `BusinessOwner`, `HungryCustomer`, and `Entertainer` inherit.
- **BusinessOwner** links to one or more **PizzaRestaurant** instances.
- **PizzaRestaurant** offers multiple **Pizza** items and may employ multiple **Entertainers**.
- **HungryCustomer** places **Order(s)**, each possibly containing multiple **Pizza** items.
- An **Order** can optionally be an **EntertainmentOrder**, which adds entertainment details and links to one **Entertainer**.
- **Entertainer** defines their availability per day for each **PizzaRestaurant** they work at.

